article.headline: Troy 87, Arkansas State 79
article.story: TROY, Ala. (AP) -- Sammy Sharp scored 25 points, hitting 11 of 15 shots, to lead Troy to an 87-79 Sun Belt Conference victory over Arkansas State on Saturday night. The Trojans (8-10, 3-4) overcame a 10-point deficit less than seven minutes into the game and pulled away by outscoring ASU (9-10, 4-3) 45-32 in the second half. Arkansas State's Adrian Banks led all scorers with 33 points, hitting on 9 of 17 shots from 3-point range. Isaac Wells had 15 points and Ryan Wedel 14 for the visitors. Troy had three others in double figures -- O'Darien Bassett 16, Richard Chaney 15 and Justin Jonus 12. Chaney also had five assists and five steals for the Trojans.
